	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Make link to wiki more prominent?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />It's easy to miss the wiki on <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://nesdev.com/">http://nesdev.com/</a><!-- m -->, and there's no indication that it has lots of up-to-date information. Would probably be a good idea to make it more prominent and add something &quot;for the most up-to-date information, see the wiki at...&quot;, so that most visitors don't go digging through old docs instead.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
