		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">lidnariq wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">it's a little goofy that we've got both <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/File:Neswires.jpg">http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/File:Neswires.jpg</a><!-- m --> and <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://nesdev.com/Ntd_8bit.jpg">http://nesdev.com/Ntd_8bit.jpg</a><!-- m --> now</div>I notice those images are similar, but not identical. The one on the wiki has additional labels and some existing labels are different.<br /><br />Direct image links: <a href="http://nesdev.com/Ntd_8bit.jpg" class="postlink">Ntd_8bit.jpg</a>, <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/images/f/f3/Neswires.jpg" class="postlink">Neswires.jpg</a>. Open the images in two different tabs, set your browser zoom to 50% or so, then flip between the tabs to see the differences.<br /><br />On the nesdev.com main page, Ntd_8bit.jpg is linked to as:<br /><ul><li> Family Computer schematic by Nintendo? File provided by Ubaldo Prones.</li></ul><br />In the wiki, Neswires.jpg is referred to as<br /><ul><li> NES wiring diagram: <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/NES_reference_guide" class="postlink">1</a>.</li><li> RF Famicom wiring diagram: <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/File_talk:Neswires.jpg" class="postlink">1</a>, <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/PPU_pin_out_and_signal_description" class="postlink">2</a></li><li> this wiring diagram: <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/PPU_rendering" class="postlink">1</a>, <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/Visual_circuit_tutorial" class="postlink">2</a>, <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/Talk:PPU_pin_out_and_signal_description" class="postlink">3</a>.</li></ul>

		

